  "type": "feat",
  "data": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>This character can no longer be flanked. This defense denies a rogue the ability to sneak attack the character by flanking her, unless the attacker has at least four more rogue levels than the target has class levels.</p>\n<p>If a character already has&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/classes/core-classes/rogue#TOC-Uncanny-Dodge-Ex-\">uncanny dodge</a>&nbsp;(see above) from another class, the levels from the classes that grant&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/classes/core-classes/rogue#TOC-Uncanny-Dodge-Ex-\">uncanny dodge</a>&nbsp;stack to determine the minimum rogue level required to flank the character.</p>",
